Manchester City begin the defence of their Premier League title away to West Ham United. Erling Haaland could make his competitive debut for his new club at the London Stadium with newly-promoted Nottingham Forest heading to Newcastle United. Fulham and Bournemouth begin their campaigns against Liverpool and Aston Villa respectively. Arsenal will begin their campaign under the lights at Selhurst Park, taking on Crystal Palace in the first game of the new season on Friday 5 August. Manchester United meanwhile begin the Erik ten Hag era at home to Brighton on the opening weekend. After beating Liverpool to the title again, City head to Anfield for the first season’s first clash between the top two on Saturday 15 October. City host Liverpool in the reverse fixture on Saturday 1 August. MORE : Aurelien Tchouameni explains reason why he chose Real Madrid over Premier League move MORE : Jamie Carragher gives Premier League clubs hope of beating Manchester City to the title despite Erling Haaland signing For more stories like this, check our sport page. Follow Metro Sport for the latest news on 
